== Spice Mixture ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} and @Hot Smoked Paprika{1%teaspoon}.

== Potatoes and Veggies ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven
to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, core, and dice
@Bell Pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and cut half the
@Red Onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges (whole onion for 4).

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}, half the spice mixture (you'll use the rest in the next
step), @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. (For 4 servings, spread potatoes across entire
baking sheet.)

Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

== Pork ==

Pat @Pork Tenderloin{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; rub all over with a
drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}, remaining spice mixture, salt, and pepper.

Once potatoes have roasted 5 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully toss bell
pepper and onion wedges on empty side with a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and
pepper; place pork on same sheet. (For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting; add
veggies and pork to a second baking sheet and roast on middle rack.)

Return to top rack until pork is cooked through and potatoes and veggies are
browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Transfer pork to a #cutting board{}; let rest at least ~{5%minutes}.

== Creamy Lemon Herb Sauce ==

Meanwhile, finely chop @Chives{} and @Parsley{}. Peel and mince or grate
@Garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

In a second small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, chives, parsley, a
squeeze of lemon juice, a pinch of garlic, and as much lemon zest as you like.
Add @Water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Taste
and season with @Salt{}, @Pepper{}, and more lemon juice if desired.

== Assembly ==

Toss together potatoes, bell pepper, and onion wedges on sheet; divide between
plates. Slice pork crosswise, then arrange over bell pepper–potato hash. Drizzle
everything with creamy lemon herb sauce. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges
on the side.